name: Space Pyrates Volume 1
description:
The first 3 volumes of the Pyrate's inaugural adventure!

Contains print only comic 'Lord Ruffington III'. Being the origins of Chewy Chewington.

We promise it's a book you can read!

name: Space Pyrates Volume 2
description:
Collecting issues 4-6 of the Pyrate's adventures. Includes epilogue comic!

If you read the first volume and discovered there was no more to read after reading it and you want to read more then do I have news for you! There IS more to read! This is the book for you I'm sure. So probably buy it. Then read it and it will be read too! Yeah!

name: Space Pyrates: Return to Catopia
description:
The Space Pyrates return for another adventure.

Winner of the 8 page non-manga category in the 2013 Comikaze 24hr Challenge.

24 pages, black & white.

name: Day One
description:
A space janitor deals with the isolation of living on an space station.  Even though it is the size of a small city. Until, one day, everything changes.

Winner of the 16 page non manga category in the 2013 Comikaze 24hr challenge.

24 pages, black & white.

name: Space Pyrates Collected Edition
description:
The printed edition of our inaugural book.

All six issues, guest art, making of and an exclusive print-only comic that you won't find in the digital edition. The book itself is just under 250 pages in length as well. Making it a big 'un. It's well worth it. We assure you. Here's a review:

"This is blissfully demented lark, up to its neck in lolcats, memes and internet humour, but all cleverly presented. Very entertaining."
Emmet O'Cuana - themomusreport.blogspot.com.au

BUT WAIT, THERE'S STILL SOME MORE THINGS.
---------------------------------------------------
All online orders come with a sketch of a character from the book. Just to sweeten the deal. We know shipping is expensive. We can't help that. But we want you to buy the book. So, FREE ART! It's enticing, no?

Choice of character will be up to whoever does the sketch (either Caitlin or Matt). So it could vary, wildly. But we guarantee maximum enjoyment for your eye balls.

But yeah, there it is, there you go.

Why are you still reading this? Why haven't you bought the book already?
